---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Jetnet Migration â€“ Bryce Kennedy">
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16 md:py-20">
    <!-- Back Navigation -->
    <a 
      href="../#projects" 
      class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-slate-300 hover:text-brand-orange transition-colors mb-8"
    >
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
        <path d="m15 18-6-6 6-6"/>
      </svg>
      Back to projects
    </a>

    <!-- Project Header -->
    <header class="space-y-4 mb-12">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 text-xs mb-4">
        <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-gray-dark/50 rounded">Angular</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-gray-dark/50 rounded">TypeScript</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-gray-dark/50 rounded">Integration</span>
      </div>
      
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold">Jetnet Migration</h1>
      
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-300">
        Led the migration from legacy intranet platform to Unily, handling complex integrations and ensuring seamless transition.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Project Content -->
    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-slate max-w-none space-y-8">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Overview</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300">
          This project involved migrating American Airlines' internal intranet from a legacy platform to Unily, 
          a modern enterprise social network. The challenge was to maintain business continuity while upgrading 
          the technology stack and improving user experience.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Challenge</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300">
          The existing Jetnet platform had grown organically over many years, resulting in:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-300 ml-4">
          <li>Complex custom integrations that needed to be preserved</li>
          <li>Thousands of content pages requiring migration</li>
          <li>High-traffic enterprise applications that couldn't experience downtime</li>
          <li>Multiple teams with varying technical capabilities needing training</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Solution</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300">
          I led the technical implementation, focusing on:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-300 ml-4">
          <li>Building custom Angular components to match existing functionality</li>
          <li>Creating integration adapters for legacy systems</li>
          <li>Developing automated content migration tools</li>
          <li>Establishing testing protocols to ensure feature parity</li>
          <li>Training and documentation for content authors and developers</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Results</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300">
          The migration was completed on schedule with minimal disruption. The new platform provided 
          improved performance, better mobile experience, and a more maintainable codebase for future 
          enhancements.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Technologies Used</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          <span class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-surface-card border border-gray-dark/70 rounded-full text-sm">Angular</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-surface-card border border-gray-dark/70 rounded-full text-sm">TypeScript</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-surface-card border border-gray-dark/70 rounded-full text-sm">Unily Platform</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-surface-card border border-gray-dark/70 rounded-full text-sm">REST APIs</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-surface-card border border-gray-dark/70 rounded-full text-sm">Node.js</span>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
